{
  "stem": "25598.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So some people-- the more privileged ones, or the sick ones, or the old ones slept on-- on this wooden thing, which we called a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] Then there was a time in which the soldier came to the house, a Romanian soldier.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he brought some money to my father-- money that was sent by these friends that my father had sent the money to, to Romania.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "That-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] --I think my father bought himself out for a week or so from the job-- from this terrible job when he-- when we got this money.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the-- the Jewish committee either-- or the Jewish committee actually had to organize these people for labor, even though we were surrounded by Romanians and Ukrainians who were ferocious.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It was the Jewish committee who had-- who had the task from them to organize whatever labor had to be done.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they took the money too, because they had organized an orphanage.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "There were a lot of kids that were roaming on the streets.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Their parents had died.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They had organized an orphanage, and they used this money to buy food or wood for-- for the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So those people who received money on a regular basis actually had it a little bit better, because they didn't have to go to labor all the time and because they could exchange the money for-- for food.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As soon as I got up, if it was in the summer, we would go out in the fields and work in the fields.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if it was in the winter, we would not.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, all day.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
